#. Tag: title
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternative Location of the Control File"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/etc/YaST2/firstboot.xml</filename> is the default path for the "
"control file, installed by the <systemitem>yast2-firstboot</systemitem> "
"package. If you need to define a different location for the control file, "
"edit <filename>/etc/sysconfig/firstboot</filename> , and change the "
"<literal>FIRSTBOOT_CONTROL_FILE</literal> variable to your preferred "
"location."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to customize more than the workflow components, refer to the "
"<filename>control.xml</filename> documentation at <link xlink:href=\"http://"
"doc.opensuse.org/projects/YaST/SLES11/tdg/inst_in_general_chap."
"html#product_control\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing &yast; Messages"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, an installation of &productname; contains several default "
"messages that are localized and displayed at certain stages of the "
"installation process. These include a welcome message, a license message, "
"and a congratulatory message at the end of installation. You can replace any "
"of these with your own versions and include localized versions of them in "
"the installation. To include your own welcome message, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "Log in as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/firstboot</filename> configuration file "
"and apply the following changes:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set <envar>FIRSTBOOT_WELCOME_DIR</envar> to the directory path where you "
"want to store the files containing the welcome message and the localized "
"versions, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "FIRSTBOOT_WELCOME_DIR=\"/usr/share/firstboot/\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your welcome message has file names other than <filename>welcome.txt</"
"filename> and <filename>welcome_<replaceable>locale</replaceable>.txt</"
"filename> (where <replaceable>locale</replaceable> matches the ISO 639 "
"language codes such as <quote>cs</quote> or <quote>de</quote> ), specify the "
"file name pattern in <envar>FIRSTBOOT_WELCOME_PATTERNS</envar> . For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "FIRSTBOOT_WELCOME_PATTERNS=\"mywelcome.txt\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If unset, the default value of <filename>welcome.txt</filename> is assumed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create the welcome file and the localized versions and place them in the "
"directory specified in the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/firstboot</filename> "
"configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Proceed in a similar way to configure customized license and finish "
"messages. These variables are <envar>FIRSTBOOT_LICENSE_DIR</envar> and "
"<envar>FIRSTBOOT_FINISH_FILE</envar> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <envar>SHOW_Y2CC_CHECKBOX</envar> to <quote>yes</quote> if the "
"user needs to be able to start &yast; directly after performing the "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing the License Action"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can customize the way the installation system reacts to a user's refusal "
"to accept the license agreement. There are three different ways which the "
"system could react to this scenario:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "halt"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The firstboot installation is aborted and the entire system shuts down. This "
"is the default setting."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "continue"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "The firstboot installation continues."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "abort"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:307
#, no-c-format
msgid "The firstboot installation is aborted, but the system attempts to boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:314
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make your choice and set <envar>LICENSE_REFUSAL_ACTION</envar> to the "
"appropriate value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing the Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on if you have changed the instance of &productname; you are "
"deploying with firstboot, you probably need to educate the end users about "
"important aspects of their new operating system. A standard installation "
"uses release notes (displayed during one of the final stages of the "
"installation) to provide important information to the users. To have your "
"own modified release notes displayed as part of a firstboot installation, "
"proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create your own release notes file. Use the RTF format as in the example "
"file in <filename>/usr/share/doc/release-notes</filename> and save the "
"result as <filename>RELEASE-NOTES.en.rtf</filename> (for English)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Store optional localized versions next to the original version and replace "
"the <literal>en</literal> part of the file name with the actual ISO 639 "
"language code, such as <literal>de</literal> for German."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_firstboot.xml:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the firstboot configuration file from <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"firstboot</filename> and set <envar>FIRSTBOOT_RELEASE_NOTES_PATH</envar> to "
"the actual directory where the release notes files are stored."
msgstr ""

